==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grog
<hw>Grog</hw> <pr>(gr⟦ocr⟧g)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named from
⟦ldquo⟧Old <ets>Grog</ets>⟦rdquo⟧ a nickname given to <person>Admiral
Vernon</person>, in allusion to his wearing a <ets>grogram</ets> cloak
in foul weather. He is said to have been the first to dilute the rum of
the sailors (about 1745).]</ety> <def>A mixture of spirit and water not
sweetened; hence, any intoxicating liquor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Grog blossom</b></col>, <cd>a redness on the nose or face
of persons who drink ardent spirits to excess.</cd>
<mark>[Collog.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Groggery</ent>⟦br⟧
